{
  "texts": [
    "Since x ′ ⊑ s x, there is a x ′′ ⊑ x ′ with x ′′ ⊑ x.",
    "By persistence, M, x ′ ⊩ φ and x ′′ ⊑ x ′ together imply M, x ′′ ⊩ φ, which with x ′′ ⊑ x implies M, x ⊮ ¬φ.Part 4 follows from part 1.In light of the similarities between ⊑ s and ⊑ observed above, it is natural to consider frames in which ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is, in the terminology of set-theoretic forcing (e.g., Jech 1986, p. 4), a separative poset.",
    "Definition 4.5 (Separative Frames).",
    "A poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is separative iff ⊑ = ⊑ s, i.e., x ⊑ y iff ∀x ′ ⊑ x ∃x ′′ ⊑ x ′: x ′′ ⊑ y.",
    "A partial-state frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ is separative iff ⟨S, ⊑⟩ is separative."
  ]
}